_tokenCalculator(address,address,uint256.details: Uses price oracle to determine exchange ratesHandles different token decimals automatically for accurate conversionFormula: amountOut = (amountIn * quotePrice * 10^tokenOutDecimal) / (basePrice * 10^tokenInDecimal)

params._tokenIn: The address of the input token
params._tokenOut: The address of the output token

returns._0: The calculated output amount in terms of the output token

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

liquidation(address,uint256).details: Only the lending pool can call this functionTransfers ownership to the liquidatorIterates through all tokens in the position and transfers their balancesHandles both wrapped native tokens and regular ERC20 tokens

params._liquidationBonus: The amount of liquidation bonus to be transferred to the liquidator
params._liquidator: The address of the liquidator who will receive all tokens

pause().details: Can only be called by accounts with OWNER_ROLE

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC-1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

repayWithSelectedToken((address,address,.details: Only the lending pool can call this functionIf the selected token is not the borrow asset, it will be swapped firstApproves lending pool to spend the borrow tokens and transfers themHandles both direct repayment and swap-then-repay scenarios

params.params: Struct containing:        - tokenIn: Address of the input token        - tokenOut: Address of the output token        - amountIn: Amount of input tokens to swap        - amountOutMinimum: Minimum amount of output tokens expected (slippage protection)

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Returns true if this contract implements the interface defined by `interfaceId`. See the corresponding https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-165#how-interfaces-are-identified[ERC section] to learn more about how these ids are created. This function call must use less than 30 000 gas.

swapTokenByPosition((address,address,uin.details: Only the lending pool can call this functionUses DEX router for token swapping with slippage protectionAutomatically registers both tokens in the position's token listReverts if insufficient balance or output amount is below minimum

params.params: Struct containing:        - tokenIn: Address of the input token        - tokenOut: Address of the output token        - amountIn: Amount of input tokens to swap        - amountOutMinimum: Minimum amount of output tokens expected (slippage protection)

returns.amountOut: The actual amount of output tokens received

swapTokenToBorrow((address,address,uint2.details: Only the lending pool can call this functionTransfers token from caller, calculates collateral needed, performs swap, and sends borrow token to lending poolApproves lending pool to spend the swapped borrow tokens

params.params: Struct containing:        - tokenIn: Address of the input token        - tokenOut: Address of the output token        - amountIn: Amount of input tokens to swap        - amountOutMinimum: Minimum amount of output tokens expected (slippage protection)        - fee: Fee amount

totalCollateral().details: Iterates through all tokens in the positionConverts each token balance to collateral token value using price oraclesSums up all token values to get total collateral

returns._0: The total collateral value denominated in the collateral token

unpause().details: Can only be called by accounts with OWNER_ROLE

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

withdrawCollateral(uint256,address).details: Only the lending pool can call this functionTransfers collateral tokens to the specified userHandles both ERC20 tokens and native tokens (unwraps if necessary)

params._user: The address of the user to receive the collateral
params.amount: The amount of collateral to withdraw

OWNER_ROLE().notice: Role identifier for accounts that have owner privileges

UPGRADER_ROLE().notice: Role identifier for accounts that can upgrade the contract

_tokenCalculator(address,address,uint256.notice: Calculates the output amount for a token swap based on price feeds

counter().notice: Counter for tracking the number of unique tokens in the position

liquidation(address,uint256).notice: Liquidates the position and transfers all tokens to the liquidator

lpAddress().notice: The address of the lending pool contract

owner().notice: The address of the position owner

pause().notice: Pauses all pausable functions in the contract

repayWithSelectedToken((address,address,.notice: Repays a loan using a selected token

swapTokenByPosition((address,address,uin.notice: Swaps tokens within the position using DEX

swapTokenToBorrow((address,address,uint2.notice: Swaps a token to the borrow token via DEX

tokenLists(uint256).notice: Mapping from token ID to token address

tokenListsId(address).notice: Mapping from token address to token ID

totalCollateral().notice: Calculates the total collateral value in the position

unpause().notice: Unpauses all pausable functions in the contract
